  - q: "What is the best dog food for heart health in the UK?"
    a: "There's no single 'heart food', but the safest evidence-based principle is a diet built on plenty of named animal protein (the natural source of taurine and its building blocks) from a manufacturer that employs a qualified nutritionist — and, for breeds genetically prone to DCM, one that doesn't lean heavily on peas, lentils and other pulses. Among the brands we review, Years stands out because every recipe is grain- AND legume-free and is formulated by a veterinary clinical nutrition specialist, which sidesteps the legume concern entirely. High-meat kibbles like Orijen and Eden supply taurine precursors naturally. If your dog already has a heart murmur or diagnosed heart disease, diet should be chosen with your vet, not from a roundup."
  - q: "Does grain-free dog food cause heart disease (DCM)?"
